definition[0]: the eastern part of a country or area
definition[1]: the countries in Asia, especially China and Japan
example[2]: Martial arts originated in the East.
definition[2]: the countries in the eastern part of Europe and Central Asia
definition[3]: the part of the US east of the Mississippi River, especially the states north of Washington DC
example[4]: She was born in the East but now lives in Atlanta.
example[5]: He was born in Utah but went to college back East.
